to upload and associate an image with each new product we need active storage
so:-
rails active_storage:install
rails db:migrate
and update app/models/product.rb to associate it with an image:
------------------------------------------------------------------
class Product < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :category
  has_one_attached :main_image # Add this line
end
------------------------------------------------------------------
then need to update your products_controller.rb to permit the new :main_image parameter
 and modify your product form (app/views/products/_form.html.erb) to include a file input field.
 To prevent errors if a product doesn't have a category assigned, it's safer to use the safe navigation operator (&.).
 This will prevent your application from crashing.

Here is the recommended code for your _product.html.erb file:
Code snippet

<%# In app/views/products/_product.html.erb %>

<p>
  <strong>Category:</strong>
  <%= product.category&.name %>
</p>

This change works because your

Product model belongs_to a Category. This association allows you to call

product.category to get the full category object and then get its name with .name.
The &. ensures that if product.category is nil, the code will return nothing instead of an error.